Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, ½ tsp @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. (You'll use the rest of the sour cream and seasoning later.) Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Place 1 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} in a #medium microwave safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30-45%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, remaining Frank's Seasoning, and a big pinch of salt and @pepper{}.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return empty #pot{} to low heat. Add a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} and scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Return potatoes to pot. Mash with 1 TBSP butter and remaining sour cream until smooth and creamy using a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and pepper. Remove from heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Place on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread chicken out across entire sheet.) Mound tops of chicken breasts with panko mixture, pressing firmly to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt and pepper. (For 4 servings, add broccoli to a second #baking sheet{}; roast chicken on top rack and broccoli on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until chicken is golden brown and cooked through and broccoli is slightly crispy, ~{18-22%minutes}.

> If broccoli is done before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

Transfer roasted broccoli to a #large bowl{}; toss with remaining butter.

Divide potatoes, chicken, and broccoli between plates. Drizzle chicken with creamy Buffalo sauce and @honey{2%teaspoon} (or serve both on the side for dipping). Sprinkle potatoes and chicken with scallion greens and serve.